# `golem/registry`

**World state:** the **`Entity`** interface (identity, type name, `Position() (x, y float32)`, `IsGlobal() bool`, `FlushUpdate` / `FullUpdate`), a thread-safe **`Registry`** (add/remove/get, `All`, `FlushAll`, `SnapshotAll`, `TickAll`), and **`FlushResult`** (spawns with IDs, deltas with IDs, removed IDs). **Opt-in entity interfaces:** `Ticker` (`Tick(dt)`), `Spawner` (`OnSpawn()`), `Remover` (`OnRemove()`), `PositionWriter` (`SetPosition(x, y float32)`)—the registry dispatches `Ticker`/`Spawner`/`Remover` automatically; `PositionWriter` is type-asserted by the collision step in `golem.Server` to write physics-corrected positions back to entities. `ReplicationDeltaEntity` supports ACK-aware generic deltas; `CompactReplicationDeltaEntity` supports compact datagram state records. `Add`/`AddOwned` call `OnSpawn` on `Spawner` entities after insertion; `DeleteEntity` calls `OnRemove` on `Remover` entities after deletion; `TickAll(dt)` calls `Tick(dt)` on every `Ticker`. All hooks run **outside** the registry mutex so hook code may safely call back into the registry. The registry tracks entity **lifecycle events** between flushes: `Add` records spawns, `DeleteEntity` records despawns. `FlushAll` returns a `FlushResult` with `SpawnIDs`/`Spawns`, `DeltaIDs`/`Deltas`, and `Removals`, then resets the tracking. `All()` returns a snapshot slice of every entity for interest-management grid updates. **Ownership tracking:** `AddOwned(entity, sessionID)` records which session owns an entity; `Owner(entityID)` looks it up; `SetOwner(entityID, sessionID)` transfers ownership (e.g. on reconnect with a new session). Game code uses **`golem.Server.CreateEntity(e, sessionID)`** (and `Owner` / `Get` on `Server`); the generated **`CommandRouter`** takes `*golem.Server` and calls those methods. The **`golem`** package does not re-export `Registry`; behavior lives here.
